reviews.review_description:
Now this blew me away. The gameplay is absolutely amazing and the story is also actually very good but has a few problems;

!!SPOILERS!!

So you take the place of (unresponsive) captain Jim, and constantly have talks with this robot (I love the robot). He really wants a kitten, so you ''give'' (the ship makes a hologram) him a kitten and he's happy. This kitten will now be on the same platform you stand, so in the midst of a fierce battle this kitten could be below the battle, just walking around. I love this. Then your home base on earth gets attacked and here's the first problem. I have lost zero battles in this game, absolutely zero. But with every battle you win your factions state gets worse, which they then blame on you. I genuintly think the developer thought this game was hard, but it really isn't. So boom your faction on earth dies because of another faction, and your ship gets attacked. You (easily) fend off the attacker, who then just gets on your ship and apparently is a red version of your robot. The robots are friends now and you have a kitten , happy ending for you, not for the people on earth (:
You get thrown out of the campaign and now A. Do Skirmishes, B. Restart the campaign (if you go to your completed campaign again it just throws you back into the main menu) or C. Do multiplayer. And since A and C aren't part of the campaign your kitten is gone );
So now I beg this legendary developer, please, make it an option for anybody who has beaten the campaign to enable the kitten for Skirmishes and Multiplayer in the options.

(oh and maybe add more levels in the campaign since the campaign is really short, but idc give me my kitten).
